                     "topFinding":  "The wave-2 god-file decomposition that dominated the last run\u0027s risk is now committed as v0.59.33 and passed the full preship gauntlet, so the acute exposure of a behavior-identical refactor of the collision/pathfinding surface sitting uncommitted and untested is gone: all six tracked god-files are under 1000 lines, the ratchet baseline matches HEAD exactly, and the game still builds, ships, saves, and plays the M1 loop with both hard-rule gates passing. That recovery lifted reliability 48 to 72, performance 68 to 82, maintainability 74 to 86, and health 78 to 82. What remains is a stack of cheap, chronic, un-actioned fixes (the dashboard audit glob has shipped null for seven runs, the em-dash entities and ASSET_SCALE_MASTER dead refs persist, LICENSES.md is still missing) plus one genuinely larger chronic gap: the extracted collision/pathfinding/navmesh and save paths have zero executing tests, so behavior-identical and crash-safe save are asserted, not verified. Now that the refactor campaign is complete, the next commit should be a player-facing M2 row, not another internal-quality pass.",
